HEADWORD: Epiphyllum
<hw>Ep`i*phyl"lum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of cactaceous plants having flattened,
jointed stems, and petals united in a tube. The flowers are very showy,
and several species are in cultivation.</def></p>

